# SCSS Module Nesting

CSS Modules in this project nest every local class under the component root. Mirror the DOM hierarchy with `>` child selectors. Do not leave sibling class blocks at the file root.

## Required

```scss
@use '@styles/variables.scss' as *;

.sectionContainer {
  // root styles...

  > .titleContainer {
    > h2 { }
    > p { }
  }

  > .itemsContainer {
    > .item {
      > .header {
        > .icon { }

        > h3 { }
      }

      > .body {
        > p { }
      }

      &[open] {
        > .header > .icon { }
      }
    }
  }
}
```

## Forbidden

```scss
// ❌ Flat sibling blocks at the root
.sectionContainer { }

.item { }

.icon { }

.item[open] > .header > .icon { }
```

## Rules

- One root class per module (the component's outer wrapper). Nest everything else under it.
- Prefer `> .child` for direct children so selectors stay tight and match the JSX tree.
- Nest pseudo-elements, pseudo-classes, and state (`&:hover`, `&[open]`, `&::before`) on the element they belong to — not as separate top-level rules.
- Keep local SCSS variables (`$toggle-size`, etc.) at the top of the file above the root class.
- Import shared tokens with `@use '@styles/variables.scss' as *;`.
- Class names used in JSX (`styles.item`) remain nested in SCSS; CSS Modules still exports them.
